-- Merkel Government Won't Raise Income, Sales Taxes, Westerwelle Tells Bild
-- Rainer Buergin
-- 2010-06-14T06:34:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/merkel-government-won-t-raise-income-sales-taxes-westerwelle-tells-bild.html

          
          
             German Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s
government has no intention of raising income tax, sales tax or
the so-called solidarity surcharge on income tax, Vice
Chancellor  Guido Westerwelle  told  Bild-Zeitung .  
 Westerwelle also told the newspaper that he wants to stay
on as foreign minister and remain chairman of the Free
Democratic Party, the second-biggest force in Merkel’s three-
party ruling coalition.  
